<h2><span style="color: white; background-color: blue;"><strong><br /></strong></span>Step 01:</h2>
<p>Students applying to the BYU-I PTA program must meet the following qualifications.&nbsp; Check to see if you are eligible to apply:</p>
<p></p>
<ul>
<li>You must demonstrate at least one semester with 12 credits or more.&nbsp; Even if you have all the pre-requisites, you will NOT be a qualified candidate if you cannot demonstrate successful completion of at least 12 credits in one semester.&nbsp;</li>
<li>Overall GPA must be 3.0 or higher.&nbsp; You must demonstrate a minimum of a "C" in pre-requisite courses.</li>
<li>You must have less than 100 credits when starting the PTA program. &nbsp;So, consider this limit when applying.&nbsp;</li>
<li>Students who already have a college degree are not eligible to apply.</li>
</ul>
<p>If you are ellible to apply, continue on to step 02...<br /><span style="color: white; background-color: blue;"><strong></strong></span></p>
<p></p>
<h2>Step 02:</h2>
<p><a href="Documents/health-recreation-human-performance/PTA program/Application_Packet.pdf" target="_blank">CLICK HERE</a> to get a .pdf of the application packet.&nbsp; Complete the forms and instructions in this packet. &nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><span style="color: white; background-color: blue;"><strong></strong></span></p>
<p></p>
